        <table id="t1602541" tblwidth="pg-wide" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Pressure Transducer Circuits Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="6">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.72in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.57in"/>
                <spanspec namest="3" nameend="6" spanname="SPAN2"/>
                <spanspec namest="4" nameend="6" spanname="S4T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="S2T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Pressure Transducer Connector (8602) Troubleshooting</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (8602) from the AC pressure transducer.</para>
                            <para>Connect the breakout box to the ESC at connector (4004).</para>
                            <para>Connect the high side gauge of the AC recovery station to the high side service
                                port.
                            </para>
                            <para>Check with Key on. The engine does not need to be running.</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>The AC system does not need to be running for these checks.</para>
                            </note>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always use breakout box ZTSE4477 to take measurements on ESC connectors.</para>
                            </note>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                            <note>
                                <para>When making resistance checks (for short circuits), always remove power and
                                    isolate the circuit being checked.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(8602) harness connector, cavity B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>5&#177;0.5 volt.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is correct, go to next step.</para>
                            <para>If voltage is incorrect, check for an open circuit between cavity B of (8602) and pin
                                27 on ESC connector (4004), or a short circuit from cavity B to ground. If the circuits
                                are ok, replace the ESC.
                            </para>
                            <note>
                                <para>If 5 volts is shorted to ground or missing out of the ESC, air pressure gauges
                                    will also read incorrectly. Pin 27 on (4004) and pin 27 on the cab 36-way connector
                                    (1600) are connected inside the ESC. A short to ground on either connector will
                                    ground out the voltage at both connectors. Refer to the
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="s08250">ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE (S08250)</hotlnk>
                                    for information on the other circuits connected to the 5 Volt reference line.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(8602) harness connector, cavity B to cavity A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>5&#177;1 volt.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is correct, go to next step.</para>
                            <para>If voltage is incorrect, check for open circuit between cavity A of (8602) and splice
                                pack (4830), or between (4830) and zero volt reference from ESC (4004) terminal 26. If
                                the circuits are ok, replace the ESC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(8602) harness connector, cavity B to cavity C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>5&#177;1 volt.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is correct, check for a short circuit from cavity C to ground. If there is
                                no short circuit, go to next step.
                            </para>
                            <para>If voltage is incorrect, check for an open circuit between cavity C of (8602) and pin
                                8 on ESC connector (4004).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Pressure Transducer Connector (8602) Troubleshooting (Continued)
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Reconnect connector (8602) to the AC pressure transducer.</para>
                            <para>Check with Key ON. The engine does not have to be running.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(4004) harness connector, cavity 8 to cavity 26.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Sense voltage</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>Measure the Sense signal voltage. Look up the equivalent pressure value in the
                                <hotlnk xrefid="t1602547">PRESSURE TRANSDUCER VOLTAGE</hotlnk>
                                table
                                <xref refid="t1602547"/>, and compare to the pressure value indicated on the AC recovery
                                station high side gauge. Values must be within 20 psi.
                            </para>
                            <para>If values disagree, replace the pressure transducer.</para>
                            <para>If values agree, replace the ESC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TROUBLESHOOTING CONCLUSION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6">
                            <para>If voltages are not present at the harness connector and there are no open or shorted
                                circuits, replace the ESC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
